  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 400°F/ Gas 6 </p>\n<p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>shallot</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span></p>\n<p>Dice the <strong>tomato</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[es]</strong></span> finely</p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>coriander </strong>finely,<strong> </strong>including the stalks</p>\n<p>Shred the <strong>little gem lettuce</strong> </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/773.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/773.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/773.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/773.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/773.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>diced shallot</strong>,<strong> tomato</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and most of the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> in a large bowl and season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Halve the <strong>lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>,<strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>squeeze in half the <strong>lime juice</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>tomato salsa</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/773.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/773.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/773.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/773.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/773.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the remaining <strong>chopped coriander</strong> to a <strong>pestle &amp; mortar</strong> (alternatively, use a food processor) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>\n<p>Bash the coriander and oil together, then add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>lime juice</strong> and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> until it forms a smooth paste – this is your <strong>lime paste</strong></p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/773.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/773.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/773.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/773.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/773.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>In a separate bowl, mix the <strong>lime</strong> <strong>paste</strong> with the <strong>mayonnaise</strong></p>\n<p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> to loosen the mix – this is your <strong>coriander</strong><strong> mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
